{"questionId":"21991","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A farmer owns a field in the shape of a triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABC</mtext></math> such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>650</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>AC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1005</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1225</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/6bb236e9e545a23bfe955bd1634c0b1c658e250b.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The local town is planning to build a highway that will intersect the borders of the field at&nbsp;points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>210</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CÊD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>°</mo></math>, as shown in the diagram below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b837e2382d85600a860a8368eaafdde6468e25b3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The town wishes to build a carpark here. They ask the farmer to exchange the part of the&nbsp;field represented by triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DCE</mtext></math>. In return the farmer will get a triangle of equal area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ADF</mtext></math>,&nbsp;where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext></math> lies on the same line as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math>, as shown in the diagram above.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DF</mtext></math>. You may assume the highway has a width of zero.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1005</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>210</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>795</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>equating answer to part (c) to area of a triangle formula &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8817</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mtext>DF</mtext><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1005</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>210</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>48</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtext>DF=</mtext></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>29</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m&nbsp;&nbsp;</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>29</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8473</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21991","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ2.2d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Estimate DF. You may assume the highway has a width of zero.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}